gh the fourteen known contemporary Brooke immigrants in VA included Robert's brothers Richard and Humphrey, the relationships of the others are unknown. Brooke family memorials remain in the Anglican church at Whitchurch, Hampshire, England."],"variants":[{"name":"Brook","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone who lived by a brook, stream, water-meadows or low, marshy ground, from Middle English <i>brook</i>, Old English <i>brōc</i> ‘brook, stream’; or a habitational name from any of various places called with this word, such as Brook (Kent, Rutland) or Brooke (Norfolk).","North German: topographic name for someone who lived by a water meadow or marsh, from Low German <i>brook</i> (cognate with German   Bruch   ‘swamp’ and Old English <i>brōc</i>; see 1 above).","Americanized form of Dutch <b>Broek</b>: topographic name from <i>broek</i>, a cognate of 2 above."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":0,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":25,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":38,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":47,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord John Brooke was born about 1290, in Somerset, England, United Kingdom, his father, Henry de Brooke IV, was 31 and his mother, Elizabeth de Gouvis, was 26. He married Joan Madston before 1320, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1347, in Doncaster, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"about 1290–1347":"umbes 1290–1347","1290–1347":"1290–1347","1298–1347":"1298–1347","1320–1368":"1320–1368","1260–1324":"1260–1324","1265–1290":"1265–1290","about 1290":"umbes 1290","before 1320":"enne 1320","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1324":"1324","1368":"1368","1289":"1289","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1265":"1265","1298":"1298","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Le Brook, Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Le Brook, Ilchester, Somerset, England":"Ilchester, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Ilchester, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Ilchester, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Doncaster, Yorkshire, England":"Doncaster, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1290–1347":"noin 1290–1347","1290–1347":"1290–1347","1298–1347":"1298–1347","1320–1368":"1320–1368","1260–1324":"1260–1324","1265–1290":"1265–1290","about 1290":"noin 1290","before 1320":"ennen vuotta 1320","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1347":"1347","1324":"1324","1368":"1368","1289":"1289","1453":"14